Expressions should not be too complex
The complexity of an expression is defined by the number of &&, || and condition ? ifTrue : ifFalse operators it contains. A single expressionâ€™s complexity should not become too high to keep the code readable. 
### Noncompliant
if (((condition1 && condition2) || (condition3 && condition4)) && condition5) { ... }
### Compliant
if ( (myFirstCondition() || mySecondCondition()) && myLastCondition()) { ... }
